    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix resource cleanup in XDMA offload error paths\n\n### Summary\nWhen the XDMA offload functions encounter errors during DMA operations, specifically in the `read_to_buffer` function, the error propagation leads to premature termination without proper resource cleanup. This results in leaked file descriptors and unmapped memory regions.\n\nThe issue manifests as \"Too many open files\" errors under sustained operation when the decoder repeatedly fails and exits without cleaning up its resources.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/nrLDPC_coding/nrLDPC_coding_xdma/nrLDPC_coding_xdma_offload.c`: \n  - Replaced `exit(1)` calls in `nrLDPC_decoder_FPGA_PYM` with proper resource cleanup via `test_dma_shutdown()`\n  - Added cleanup calls for both error and success paths\n  - Reset `init_flag` to ensure proper re-initialization on subsequent calls\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Configure the LDPC decoder to use XDMA offload\n2. Introduce errors in the DMA read path (e.g., disconnect FPGA device)\n3. Run continuous decoding operations\n4. Observe growing number of open file descriptors using `lsof` or memory mappings with `pmap`\n5. Eventually see \"Too many open files\" errors in the logs\n\n"
}